  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study evaluates the efficacy and tolerability of alternating short cycles of high-dose
      and conventional chemotherapy in combination with rituximab in CD20 positive patients,
      followed by local radiation therapy in the case of initial mediastinal or central nervous
      system (CNS) involvement or a residual tumor after chemotherapy. A dose-reduced regimen is
      offered for patients estimated to be over 55 years, biologically.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
